  "text": "Since it originally has no D0-brane charge, the dual fundamental string has the vanishing winding number along x 9 -direction. The mass of this fundamental string is, of course, equal to the distance between two D5-branes, [CITATION_1] while the mass of the original D2-brane is proportional to |z|. So, we find that the distance between two D5-branes in Fig 1 can be written as |z| up to a prefactor. To be more precise, if we set x 8 and x 9 so that the D5' is located at the origin on the x 8 -x 9 plane, the position of the D5 is determined by",
